  <front>
   <head>An Hymn to Sleep. Written when the Author was sick.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, pow'rful Deity,</l>
     <l n="2" met="+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Mortals owe their Bliss to thee.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">How long shall I thy Absence mourn,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And when be bless'd in thy Return?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Relentless God! why will you flee,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And take Delight to torture me:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or do you kindly flight my Pray'r,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To make me for my Change prepare?</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis well this Happiness remains;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When you resuse to ease our Pains,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Your Brother  your Place supplies,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And kindly seals the Wretch's Eyes.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
